---
import Layout from "../layouts/main.astro";
---

<Layout title="Why I Write">
  <section class="relative z-20 w-full max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-16 px-7 md:mt-24 lg:mt-28 xl:px-0">

    <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-violet-500 dark:text-violet-400">
      Why I Write
    </p>
    <h1 class="mb-8 text-4xl font-bold leading-tight dark:text-white lg:text-5xl">
      I write because I want to connect.
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
      <p>
        To share what I'm thinking about, find others who are wrestling with the same questions, and learn together. If something here resonates with you, I'd love to hear from you.
      </p>
      <p>
        Writing is how I process what I'm learning — about AI, about building, about the intersection of data and human behavior. Putting ideas into words forces clarity in a way that thinking alone never quite does. This is my running document of what I'm figuring out.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm looking for people who are deep in this space — builders, researchers, strategists, curious minds who are as energized by what's happening in AI as I am. If you're experimenting with agents, figuring out how to apply these tools in meaningful ways, or just trying to make sense of a field that's moving faster than anyone can fully track, I want to find you.
      </p>
      <p>
        I write to share what I know, because knowledge compounds when you put it in circulation. And I write to build a body of work that reflects how I think — not just what I've done, but how I approach problems, what questions I'm asking, and where I think things are going.
      </p>
      <p>
        And while AI is a big part of what I write about, it's not the whole picture. I'm also keenly interested in science — particularly the research and data challenges that come with it. Information and product management are woven through everything I do professionally. And then there's sports, my favorite form of reality TV — the strategy, the competition, the completely unscripted human drama of it all.
      </p>
      <p>
        If something here is useful to you, that's the point. If it sparks a conversation, even better.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a
        href="/posts"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold rounded-full bg-neutral-900 dark:bg-white text-white dark:text-neutral-900 hover:bg-neutral-700 dark:hover:bg-neutral-200 transition-colors duration-200"
      >
        Read the blog
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
      <a
        href="mailto:amy@zencloud.io"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold rounded-full border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 hover:bg-neutral-100 dark:hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors duration-200"
      >
        Get in touch
      </a>
    </div>

  </section>
</Layout>
